.TH RUFUSARM64-CLI 1 "20 July 2026" "RufusArm64 0.13.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rufusarm64-cli \- inspect images and safely create bootable USB media on Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rufusarm64-cli list
.RI [ --all ]
.RI [ --json ]
.PP
.B rufusarm64-cli inspect
.BI --image " FILE"
.RI [ --json ]
.PP
.B rufusarm64-cli hash
.RI [ --algorithm " md5|sha1|sha256|sha512" ]
.RI [ --all ]
.RI [ --json ]
.I FILE
.PP
.B sudo rufusarm64-cli write
.BI --image " FILE"
.BI --device " /dev/DEVICE"
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B rufusarm64-cli acquire
.RI "verify|list|download|channel list|channel download"
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B rufusarm64-cli uefi
.RI "validate|integrity manifest|integrity verify"
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B rufusarm64-cli persistence
.RI "plan|analyze"
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B sudo rufusarm64-cli qualify
.RI "start|verify"
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rufusarm64-cli
is the native helper and troubleshooting interface used by RufusArm64. It
writes recognized GPT/MBR disk images and Linux ISOHybrid media directly,
prepares supported compressed and virtual-disk inputs, and creates extracted
Windows installation media using GPT or MBR, UEFI or x86-family BIOS/CSM, and
Automatic, FAT32, or NTFS selection.
.PP
The graphical application supplies exact source and target identities, guarded
cancellation, and fresh Polkit authorization. Direct terminal use must retain
the same safety boundary and verify the exact whole-disk path before writing.
.SH IMAGE INSPECTION AND CHECKSUMS
.B list
returns eligible whole devices and identity tokens. The default view excludes
ordinary fixed disks and the running system disk.
.PP
.B inspect
performs read-only recognition of supported image and container formats. JSON
output remains available when an unusable image produces a nonzero status.
.PP
.B hash
reads one identity-bound regular-file descriptor. With no options it computes
SHA-256. Use repeated
.B --algorithm
or
.B --all
to calculate the ordered MD5, SHA-1, SHA-256, and SHA-512 comparison set. MD5
and SHA-1 are legacy comparison values only and are never used for acquisition
trust or destructive-write assurance.
.SH COMMON WRITE OPTIONS
.TP
.B --verify
Flush block buffers and compare copied data after writing. Recommended.
.TP
.BI --partition-scheme " gpt|mbr"
Choose the Windows-media partition table. GPT is the default.
.TP
.BI --target-system " uefi|bios"
Choose UEFI or legacy BIOS/UEFI-CSM. Windows ARM64 is UEFI-only.
.TP
.BI --filesystem " auto|fat32|ntfs"
Choose the Windows-media filesystem. Automatic prefers FAT32 when safe and
otherwise selects NTFS. FAT32 can split oversized WIM or ESD payloads.
.TP
.BI --cluster-size " SIZE"
Select a supported Windows filesystem allocation unit.
.TP
.BI --label " LABEL"
Set the validated target volume label where the selected mode supports it.
.TP
.BI --driver-folder " DIRECTORY"
Validate and stage Windows driver packages for Windows PE and manual Setup use.
.TP
.BI --dbx-file " FILE"
Reject Windows EFI boot files revoked by the selected Secure Boot DBX. Firmware
is not modified.
.TP
.B --full-format
Zero-write the new Windows data partition before formatting.
.TP
.B --bad-block-check
Zero-write and read back the complete new Windows data partition before format.
.TP
.BI --expected-identity " TOKEN"
Require the refreshed target identity returned by
.BR "rufusarm64-cli list --json" .
The graphical workflows always supply this value.
.TP
.B --yes
Skip terminal confirmation. This never bypasses identity or target-policy
checks and is intended for reviewed automation.
.TP
.B --allow-fixed
Permit an explicitly selected non-removable whole disk for direct terminal use.
The running system disk and protected mounts remain refused. Graphical paths do
not expose this option.
.TP
.B --no-unmount
Refuse mounted descendants rather than unmounting eligible removable media.
.SH LINUX PERSISTENCE
.B persistence plan
analyzes a caller-mounted media tree without opening a target device.
.B persistence analyze
mounts the exact identity-bound source image read-only and returns the same
bounded plan used by creation.
.PP
The guarded creator supports a narrow Ubuntu casper and Debian live-boot
contract: a fresh GPT, writable FAT32 boot partition, ext4 persistence
partition, architecture-matching fallback UEFI loader, FAT32-safe media tree,
and at least 1 GiB of persistence capacity. Unsupported boot layouts, unsafe
links, oversized FAT32 files, compressed inputs, encrypted persistence, and
MBR/BIOS persistence are refused.
.PP
The direct writer requires both
.B --mode linux-persistent
and
.B --experimental-persistence .
The installed graphical workflow uses its separate package-owned helper.
.PP
.B qualify start
and
.B qualify verify
record an observed boot and later reboot of the same persistent USB. Passing
qualification proves only the exact image, USB, controller, firmware, and
computer that were observed.
.SH SIGNED IMAGE ACQUISITION
Local acquisition commands validate detached Ed25519-signed catalogues.
Built-in channel commands use package-owned threshold-root metadata, monotonic
rollback protection, expiry checks, verified cache fallback, HTTPS and redirect
host restrictions, exact size, SHA-256, storage-space preflight, and atomic
installation.
.PP
Resumable mode retains only an owner-private partial bound to the signed image
identity and rehashes it before reuse. Cancellation or failure never installs
an unverified image. The production built-in channel remains disabled until
reviewed public mirrors and offline trust metadata are provisioned.
.SH UEFI MEDIA VALIDATION
.B uefi validate
performs a bounded descriptor-rooted read-only scan of mounted or extracted
media. It checks the architecture fallback loader, PE/EFI structure, optional
DBX image and certificate revocations, SBAT metadata, and trusted local or
running-firmware SBAT levels. It never modifies firmware or media.
.PP
.B uefi integrity manifest
creates exact uefi-md5sum-compatible manifest text from a bounded read-only
scan.
.B uefi integrity verify
checks the root `md5sum.txt` and reports changed, missing, unexpected, and byte
count mismatches. MD5 is used only for compatibility with the optional
boot-time validator; SHA-256 remains the trust primitive elsewhere.
.SH WINDOWS SETUP ANALYSIS
Before optional Windows setup customizations, the identity-bound ISO is mounted
read-only and its complete installation metadata is inspected. Every WIM/ESD
edition must agree on Windows generation, client/server family, and
architecture. Existing split SWM sequences must be complete and unambiguous.
The graphical options summary reports bounded edition names/count, payload
kind, and part count. Unknown or conflicting metadata disables customizations
without blocking ordinary no-customization media creation.
.SH SAFETY
The program refuses partitions, read-only targets, the running root disk, and
an image stored on the selected target. It retains and hashes the selected
source, revalidates target identity immediately before destructive work, locks
the target, rejects unsafe symbolic-link traversal, flushes buffers, and checks
copied files, media structures, and filesystems. Cancellation leaves changed
incomplete media explicitly unqualified.
.PP
Software verification does not prove physical boot, persistence on untested
hardware, or Secure Boot compatibility for the unsigned package-owned
uefi-md5sum loader.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Zero indicates success. A nonzero status indicates refusal, cancellation,
validation failure, I/O failure, filesystem failure, or verification mismatch.
